You're much better off focussing relentlessly one one, until you're fluent in that language.

Then turn to the other.

#datascience #Python #rstats

If you want to be a great data scientist, it's probably best to learn both R and Python in the long run.

But in the short run, it's better if you focus.

#datascience #Python #rstats

For example, you'll get confused by:

– groupby (Python) vs group_by (R)
– filter (which retrieves columns in Python) vs filter (which retrieves rows in R)

#datascience #Python #rstats

Just a reminder: 

Learning R and Python at the same time will confuse you and impede your progress.

#datascience #rstats #Python

Python is a better data technology language.

R is a better data analytics language.
